  "title": "SQL Server Permission Model",
  "contentHtml": "In this episode Michael talks with guest Andreas Wolter&nbsp;\n                        (\n                           <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href='https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreaswolter/'><i class=\"fa-brands fa-linkedin\"></i></a>\n                           <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href='https://twitter.com/AndreasWolter'><i class=\"fa-brands fa-x-twitter\"></i></a>\n                        ) \n                        about SQL Server and Azure SQL Database permissions. If you have never gotten your head around SQL Server permissions, you came to right place! Andreas and Michael are colleagues in the Azure Data Platform.\n      \n                        <br><br>\n      \n                        <!-- Insert episode info from rss.com into NNNNNN and TTTTTT which is the episode number and the title -->\n                        <iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://player.rss.com/azsecpodcast/656745?theme=light\" class=\"podcast-player\" title=\"The Azure Security Podcast\" frameborder=\"0\"><a href=\"https://rss.com/podcasts/azsecpodcast/656745/\">SQLPerm</a></iframe>\n      \n                        <h5>Links</h5> \n                        <!-- Links to news articles -->\n                        <ul>\n                           <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href='https://rss.com/podcasts/azsecpodcast/656745/'>Transcript <i class=\"fa-solid fa-pencil\"></i></a></li>\n                           <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/azure-sql-blog/security-the-principle-of-least-privilege-polp/ba-p/2067390\">Security: The Principle of Least Privilege (POLP)</a></li>\n                           <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/azure-sql-blog/private-preview-controlling-access-to-azure-sql-at-scale-with/ba-p/2945491\">Private Preview: controlling access to Azure SQL at scale with policies in Purview</a></li>\n                           <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/azure-sql-blog/new-granular-permissions-for-sql-server-2022-and-azure-sql-to/ba-p/3607622\">New granular permissions for SQL Server 2022 and Azure SQL to improve adherence with PoLP </a></li>\n                           <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/azure-sql-blog/revamped-sql-permission-system-for-principle-of-least-privilege/ba-p/3639399\">Revamped SQL Permission system for Principle of Least Privilege and external policies – internals</a></li>\n                           <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"http://andreas-wolter.com/en/schema-design-for-sql-server-recommendations-for-schema-design-with-security-in-mind/\">Schema-design for SQL Server: recommendations for Schema design with security in mind                     </a></li>\n                           <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/relational-databases/tutorial-ownership-chains-and-context-switching?view=sql-server-ver16\">Tutorial: Ownership Chains and Context Switching</a></li>\n      \n                        </ul>"
